This paper deals with the problem of synthesizing optimal strategies in stochastic games, which is a topic that falls under game theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses the use of Rabin winning conditions, which is a topic in logic and automata theory (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper proposes an algorithm to compute optimal strategies, which involves computational techniques such as dynamic programming and graph algorithms, making it relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper deals with the interaction between a system and its environment, which is a topic in control theory and systems engineering (cs.SY).
